# Kconfig — Decawave DW1000 UWB transceiver driver
#
# Sourced from the application root Kconfig.

config DW1000
	bool "Decawave DW1000 UWB transceiver driver (vendored)"
	select SPI
	select GPIO
	help
	  Enable the vendored Decawave DW1000 register/device API
	  (deca_device.c + deca_params_init.c) together with the Zephyr SPI and
	  GPIO port layer (deca_port.c, UWB-93).

	  Automatically selects CONFIG_SPI (nRF SPIM driver) and CONFIG_GPIO
	  (GPIO subsystem) so application code does not need to enable them
	  explicitly.

	  The port layer reads the DW1000 SPI device node from the devicetree
	  using the label 'dw1000' (compatible = "decawave,dw1000") and obtains
	  the SPI bus config, CS GPIO, IRQ GPIO, and RESET GPIO from DT properties.

	  The SPI port functions (writetospi, readfromspi), interrupt mutex
	  (decamutexon/decamutexoff), and millisecond delay (deca_sleep) are
	  provided as strong definitions in port/deca_port.c; the __weak stubs in
	  port/deca_port_stub.c are overridden at link time.

	  Call dw1000_port_init() once during application start-up before using
	  any deca_driver or port functions.
